            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Bob Spins A Yarn</head>
                <origin>Religious Telegraph (Dayton, OH)</origin>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <commentary>"An unknown correspondent enclosed the following rich paragraph to a
                    gentleman of this place, without comment. It is an extract from the 'Religious
                    Telegraph,' an abolition paper published at Dayton, OH. . . . . It will be seen
                    from the above that Bob has lost none of his shrewdness and knavery. . . ."</commentary>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Napper</ln>
                        <fn>Robert</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Enclosure tells story of Robert Napper, formerly a slave in Augusta County
                    who earned his freedom, moved to Ohio and subsequently purchased his wife and
                    one child. He is seeking help in getting enough money to purchase his remaining
                    four children. Spectator's comments are harsh, accusing him of being a thief.</summary>
                <note>aubrowser/ssaug59.html#8.23b</note>
            </div>
